  "text": "Simulation. In this section, axial slices of real and simulated PET images, before and after CT-AC correction, are shown. More precisely, Figure 4 shows a transaxial slice of original PET and CT-AC images of the rat-sized phantom. Profiles traced across them are shown in Figure 6 . They show a count increment of about 40%, and the flatnesses calculated according to (5) for corrected and uncorrected images are about 1% and 22%, respectively. Figure 5 shows an axial . Only in this case images were reconstructed using OSEM 3D [CITATION_1] .",
